aly (Eds.) Tonminerale und Tone; Tamura, T., Identification of clay minerals from acid soils (1958) Journal of Soil Science, 9, pp. 141-147; Trommsdorff, V., Dietrich, V., Grundzüge der Erdwissenschaften (1999) vdf-Verlag, 6. , Auflage, Zürich, Switzerland; Turpault, M.-P., Righi, D., Utérano, C., Clay minerals: precise markers of the spatial and temporal variability of the biogeochemical soil environment (2008) Geoderma, 147 (3-4), pp. 108-115; Van der Marel, H.W., Beutelspacher, H., (1976) Atlas of Infrared Spectroscopy of Clay Minerals and Their Admixtures, , Elsevier Scientific Publishing Company, Amsterdam-Oxford-New York; Vantelon, D., Pelletier, M., Michot, L.J., Barres, O., Thomas, F., Fe, Mg and Al distribution in the octahedral sheet of montmorillonites. An infrared study in the OH-bending region (2001) Clay Minerals, 36, pp. 369-379; Wadham, J.L., Cooper, R.J., Tranter, M., Hodgkins, R., Enhancement of glacial solute fluxes in the proglacial zone of a polythermal glacier (2001) Journal of Glaciology, 47, pp. 378-386; Wilkinson, M.T., Chappell, J., Humphreys, G.S., Fifield, K., Smith, B., Hesse, P.P., Soil production in heath and forest, Blue Mountains, Australia: influence of lithology and palaeoclimate (2005) Earth Surface Processes and Landforms, 30, pp. 923-934; Wilson, M.J., (1994) Clay Mineralogy: Spectroscopic and Chemical Determinative Methods, , Chapman & Hall, London","Egli, M.; Department of Geography, University of Zurich, Zurich, 8057, Switzerland; email: markus.egli@geo.uzh.ch",,,,,,,,00167061,,GEDMA,,"English","Geoderma",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-80051697200
